<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 511.4A1/1480.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Delegate <persName type="from">Van Dyke</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Germany and Portugal decline to put the Convention into effect until
                            Turkey, Greece and Serbia come in; Great Britain will wait for Germany.
                            Yesterday’s meeting adjourned till Monday. May we agree to put the
                            Convention into effect with a limited number of Powers?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Van Dyke</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>